data.title: John Hennessy Saul
data.meta_description: John Hennessy Saul was an Irish-born American horticulturist and landscape architect who assisted in the planning and the development of the National Mall in Washington, D.C., and served as the first chairman of Washington, D.C.’s parks commission.
